defs.docs: An experimental byte string library.

defs.name: BStr
defs.docs: A wrapper for `&[u8]` that provides convenient string oriented trait impls.

defs.name: BString
defs.docs:
A wrapper for `Vec<u8>` that provides convenient string oriented trait
 impls.

defs.name: B
defs.docs: A short-hand constructor for building a `&[u8]`.

defs.name: Sealed
defs.docs:
Ensure that callers cannot implement `ByteSlice` by making an
 umplementable trait its super trait.

defs.name: ByteSlice
defs.docs: A trait that extends `&[u8]` with string oriented methods.

defs.name: as_bytes
defs.docs:
A method for accessing the raw bytes of this type. This is always a
 no-op and callers shouldn't care about it. This only exists for making
 the extension trait work.

defs.name: as_bytes_mut
defs.docs:
A method for accessing the raw bytes of this type, mutably. This is
 always a no-op and callers shouldn't care about it. This only exists
 for making the extension trait work.

defs.name: as_bstr
defs.docs: Return this byte slice as a `&BStr`.

defs.name: as_bstr_mut
defs.docs: Return this byte slice as a `&mut BStr`.

defs.name: from_os_str
defs.docs: Create an immutable byte string from an OS string slice.

defs.name: from_path
defs.docs: Create an immutable byte string from a file path.

defs.name: to_str
defs.docs: Safely convert this byte string into a `&str` if it's valid UTF-8.

defs.name: to_str_unchecked
defs.docs:
Unsafely convert this byte string into a `&str`, without checking for
 valid UTF-8.

defs.name: to_str_lossy
defs.docs:
Convert this byte string to a valid UTF-8 string by replacing invalid
 UTF-8 bytes with the Unicode replacement codepoint (`U+FFFD`).

defs.name: to_str_lossy_into
defs.docs:
Copy the contents of this byte string into the given owned string
 buffer, while replacing invalid UTF-8 code unit sequences with the
 Unicode replacement codepoint (`U+FFFD`).

defs.name: to_os_str
defs.docs: Create an OS string slice from this byte string.

defs.name: to_os_str_lossy
defs.docs: Lossily create an OS string slice from this byte string.

defs.name: to_path
defs.docs: Create a path slice from this byte string.

defs.name: to_path_lossy
defs.docs: Lossily create a path slice from this byte string.

defs.name: repeatn
defs.docs: Create a new byte string by repeating this byte string `n` times.

defs.name: contains_str
defs.docs: Returns true if and only if this byte string contains the given needle.

defs.name: starts_with_str
defs.docs: Returns true if and only if this byte string has the given prefix.

defs.name: ends_with_str
defs.docs: Returns true if and only if this byte string has the given suffix.

defs.name: find
defs.docs: Returns the index of the first occurrence of the given needle.

defs.name: rfind
defs.docs: Returns the index of the last occurrence of the given needle.

defs.name: find_iter
defs.value: fn <'a, B> (&'a self, needle: &'a B) -> Find<'a>
defs.docs:
Returns an iterator of the non-overlapping occurrences of the given
 needle. The iterator yields byte offset positions indicating the start
 of each match.

defs.name: rfind_iter
defs.value: fn <'a, B> (&'a self, needle: &'a B) -> FindReverse<'a>
defs.docs:
Returns an iterator of the non-overlapping occurrences of the given
 needle in reverse. The iterator yields byte offset positions indicating
 the start of each match.

defs.name: find_byte
defs.docs:
Returns the index of the first occurrence of the given byte. If the
 byte does not occur in this byte string, then `None` is returned.

defs.name: rfind_byte
defs.docs:
Returns the index of the last occurrence of the given byte. If the
 byte does not occur in this byte string, then `None` is returned.

defs.name: find_char
defs.docs:
Returns the index of the first occurrence of the given codepoint.
 If the codepoint does not occur in this byte string, then `None` is
 returned.

defs.name: rfind_char
defs.docs:
Returns the index of the last occurrence of the given codepoint.
 If the codepoint does not occur in this byte string, then `None` is
 returned.

defs.name: find_byteset
defs.docs:
Returns the index of the first occurrence of any of the bytes in the
 provided set.

defs.name: find_not_byteset
defs.docs:
Returns the index of the first occurrence of a byte that is not a member
 of the provided set.

defs.name: rfind_byteset
defs.docs:
Returns the index of the last occurrence of any of the bytes in the
 provided set.

defs.name: rfind_not_byteset
defs.docs:
Returns the index of the last occurrence of a byte that is not a member
 of the provided set.

defs.name: fields
defs.docs:
Returns an iterator over the fields in a byte string, separated by
 contiguous whitespace.

defs.name: fields_with
defs.docs:
Returns an iterator over the fields in a byte string, separated by
 contiguous codepoints satisfying the given predicate.

defs.name: split_str
defs.value: fn <'a, B> (&'a self, splitter: &'a B) -> Split<'a>
defs.docs:
Returns an iterator over substrings of this byte string, separated
 by the given byte string. Each element yielded is guaranteed not to
 include the splitter substring.

defs.name: rsplit_str
defs.value: fn <'a, B> (&'a self, splitter: &'a B) -> SplitReverse<'a>
defs.docs:
Returns an iterator over substrings of this byte string, separated by
 the given byte string, in reverse. Each element yielded is guaranteed
 not to include the splitter substring.

defs.name: splitn_str
defs.value: fn <'a, B> (&'a self, limit: usize, splitter: &'a B) -> SplitN<'a>
defs.docs:
Returns an iterator of at most `limit` substrings of this byte string,
 separated by the given byte string. If `limit` substrings are yielded,
 then the last substring will contain the remainder of this byte string.

defs.name: rsplitn_str
defs.value: fn <'a, B> (&'a self, limit: usize, splitter: &'a B) -> SplitNReverse<'a>
defs.docs:
Returns an iterator of at most `limit` substrings of this byte string,
 separated by the given byte string, in reverse. If `limit` substrings
 are yielded, then the last substring will contain the remainder of this
 byte string.

defs.name: replace
defs.value: fn <N, R> (&self, needle: N, replacement: R) -> Vec<u8>
defs.docs:
Replace all matches of the given needle with the given replacement, and
 the result as a new `Vec<u8>`.

defs.name: replacen
defs.value: fn <N, R> (&self, needle: N, replacement: R, limit: usize) -> Vec<u8>
defs.docs:
Replace up to `limit` matches of the given needle with the given
 replacement, and the result as a new `Vec<u8>`.

defs.name: replace_into
defs.value: fn <N, R> (&self, needle: N, replacement: R, dest: &mut Vec<u8>) -> ()
defs.docs:
Replace all matches of the given needle with the given replacement,
 and write the result into the provided `Vec<u8>`.

defs.name: replacen_into
defs.value: fn <N, R> (&self, needle: N, replacement: R, limit: usize, dest: &mut Vec<u8>) -> ()
defs.docs:
Replace up to `limit` matches of the given needle with the given
 replacement, and write the result into the provided `Vec<u8>`.

defs.name: bytes
defs.docs: Returns an iterator over the bytes in this byte string.

defs.name: chars
defs.docs:
Returns an iterator over the Unicode scalar values in this byte string.
 If invalid UTF-8 is encountered, then the Unicode replacement codepoint
 is yielded instead.

defs.name: char_indices
defs.docs:
Returns an iterator over the Unicode scalar values in this byte string
 along with their starting and ending byte index positions. If invalid
 UTF-8 is encountered, then the Unicode replacement codepoint is yielded
 instead.

defs.name: graphemes
defs.docs:
Returns an iterator over the grapheme clusters in this byte string.
 If invalid UTF-8 is encountered, then the Unicode replacement codepoint
 is yielded instead.

defs.name: grapheme_indices
defs.docs:
Returns an iterator over the grapheme clusters in this byte string
 along with their starting and ending byte index positions. If invalid
 UTF-8 is encountered, then the Unicode replacement codepoint is yielded
 instead.

defs.name: words
defs.docs:
Returns an iterator over the words in this byte string. If invalid
 UTF-8 is encountered, then the Unicode replacement codepoint is yielded
 instead.

defs.name: word_indices
defs.docs:
Returns an iterator over the words in this byte string along with
 their starting and ending byte index positions.

defs.name: words_with_breaks
defs.docs:
Returns an iterator over the words in this byte string, along with
 all breaks between the words. Concatenating all elements yielded by
 the iterator results in the original string (modulo Unicode replacement
 codepoint substitutions if invalid UTF-8 is encountered).

defs.name: words_with_break_indices
defs.docs:
Returns an iterator over the words and their byte offsets in this
 byte string, along with all breaks between the words. Concatenating
 all elements yielded by the iterator results in the original string
 (modulo Unicode replacement codepoint substitutions if invalid UTF-8 is
 encountered).

defs.name: sentences
defs.docs: Returns an iterator over the sentences in this byte string.

defs.name: sentence_indices
defs.docs:
Returns an iterator over the sentences in this byte string along with
 their starting and ending byte index positions.

defs.name: lines
defs.docs:
An iterator over all lines in a byte string, without their
 terminators.

defs.name: lines_with_terminator
defs.docs:
An iterator over all lines in a byte string, including their
 terminators.

defs.name: trim
defs.docs:
Return a byte string slice with leading and trailing whitespace
 removed.

defs.name: trim_start
defs.docs: Return a byte string slice with leading whitespace removed.

defs.name: trim_end
defs.docs: Return a byte string slice with trailing whitespace removed.

defs.name: trim_with
defs.docs:
Return a byte string slice with leading and trailing characters
 satisfying the given predicate removed.

defs.name: trim_start_with
defs.docs:
Return a byte string slice with leading characters satisfying the given
 predicate removed.

defs.name: trim_end_with
defs.docs:
Return a byte string slice with trailing characters satisfying the
 given predicate removed.

defs.name: to_lowercase
defs.docs:
Returns a new `Vec<u8>` containing the lowercase equivalent of this
 byte string.

defs.name: to_lowercase_into
defs.docs:
Writes the lowercase equivalent of this byte string into the given
 buffer. The buffer is not cleared before written to.

defs.name: to_ascii_lowercase
defs.docs:
Returns a new `Vec<u8>` containing the ASCII lowercase equivalent of
 this byte string.

defs.name: make_ascii_lowercase
defs.docs: Convert this byte string to its lowercase ASCII equivalent in place.

defs.name: to_uppercase
defs.docs:
Returns a new `Vec<u8>` containing the uppercase equivalent of this
 byte string.

defs.name: to_uppercase_into
defs.docs:
Writes the uppercase equivalent of this byte string into the given
 buffer. The buffer is not cleared before written to.

defs.name: to_ascii_uppercase
defs.docs:
Returns a new `Vec<u8>` containing the ASCII uppercase equivalent of
 this byte string.

defs.name: make_ascii_uppercase
defs.docs: Convert this byte string to its uppercase ASCII equivalent in place.

defs.name: reverse_bytes
defs.docs: Reverse the bytes in this string, in place.

defs.name: reverse_chars
defs.docs: Reverse the codepoints in this string, in place.

defs.name: reverse_graphemes
defs.docs: Reverse the graphemes in this string, in place.

defs.name: is_ascii
defs.docs: Returns true if and only if every byte in this byte string is ASCII.

defs.name: is_utf8
defs.docs: Returns true if and only if the entire byte string is valid UTF-8.

defs.name: last_byte
defs.docs:
Returns the last byte in this byte string, if it's non-empty. If this
 byte string is empty, this returns `None`.

defs.name: find_non_ascii_byte
defs.docs:
Returns the index of the first non-ASCII byte in this byte string (if
 any such indices exist). Specifically, it returns the index of the
 first byte with a value greater than or equal to `0x80`.

defs.name: copy_within_str
defs.value: fn <R> (&mut self, src: R, dest: usize) -> ()
defs.docs:
Copies elements from one part of the slice to another part of itself,
 where the parts may be overlapping.

defs.name: Finder
defs.docs: A single substring searcher fixed to a particular needle.

defs.name: new
defs.docs: Create a new finder for the given needle.

defs.name: into_owned
defs.docs:
Convert this finder into its owned variant, such that it no longer
 borrows the needle.

defs.name: needle
defs.docs: Returns the needle that this finder searches for.

defs.name: find
defs.docs:
Returns the index of the first occurrence of this needle in the given
 haystack.

defs.name: FinderReverse
defs.docs: A single substring reverse searcher fixed to a particular needle.

defs.name: new
defs.docs: Create a new reverse finder for the given needle.

defs.name: into_owned
defs.docs:
Convert this finder into its owned variant, such that it no longer
 borrows the needle.

defs.name: needle
defs.docs: Returns the needle that this finder searches for.

defs.name: rfind
defs.docs:
Returns the index of the last occurrence of this needle in the given
 haystack.

defs.name: Find
defs.docs: An iterator over non-overlapping substring matches.

defs.name: FindReverse
defs.docs: An iterator over non-overlapping substring matches in reverse.

defs.name: Bytes
defs.docs: An iterator over the bytes in a byte string.

defs.name: Fields
defs.docs: An iterator over the fields in a byte string, separated by whitespace.

defs.name: FieldsWith
defs.docs:
An iterator over fields in the byte string, separated by a predicate over
 codepoints.

defs.name: Split
defs.docs: An iterator over substrings in a byte string, split by a separator.

defs.name: SplitReverse
defs.docs:
An iterator over substrings in a byte string, split by a separator, in
 reverse.

defs.name: SplitN
defs.docs:
An iterator over at most `n` substrings in a byte string, split by a
 separator.

defs.name: SplitNReverse
defs.docs:
An iterator over at most `n` substrings in a byte string, split by a
 separator, in reverse.

defs.name: Lines
defs.docs: An iterator over all lines in a byte string, without their terminators.

defs.name: LinesWithTerminator
defs.docs: An iterator over all lines in a byte string, including their terminators.

defs.name: concat
defs.docs:
Concatenate the elements given by the iterator together into a single
 `Vec<u8>`.

defs.name: join
defs.value: fn <B, T, I> (separator: B, elements: I) -> Vec<u8>
defs.docs:
Join the elements given by the iterator with the given separator into a
 single `Vec<u8>`.

defs.name: Sealed
defs.docs:
Ensure that callers cannot implement `ByteSlice` by making an
 umplementable trait its super trait.

defs.name: ByteVec
defs.docs: A trait that extends `Vec<u8>` with string oriented methods.

defs.name: as_vec
defs.docs:
A method for accessing the raw vector bytes of this type. This is
 always a no-op and callers shouldn't care about it. This only exists
 for making the extension trait work.

defs.name: as_vec_mut
defs.docs:
A method for accessing the raw vector bytes of this type, mutably. This
 is always a no-op and callers shouldn't care about it. This only exists
 for making the extension trait work.

defs.name: into_vec
defs.docs:
A method for consuming ownership of this vector. This is always a no-op
 and callers shouldn't care about it. This only exists for making the
 extension trait work.

defs.name: from_slice
defs.docs: Create a new owned byte string from the given byte slice.

defs.name: from_os_string
defs.docs: Create a new byte string from an owned OS string.

defs.name: from_os_str_lossy
defs.docs: Lossily create a new byte string from an OS string slice.

defs.name: from_path_buf
defs.docs: Create a new byte string from an owned file path.

defs.name: from_path_lossy
defs.docs: Lossily create a new byte string from a file path.

defs.name: push_byte
defs.docs: Appends the given byte to the end of this byte string.

defs.name: push_char
defs.docs: Appends the given `char` to the end of this byte string.

defs.name: push_str
defs.docs:
Appends the given slice to the end of this byte string. This accepts
 any type that be converted to a `&[u8]`. This includes, but is not
 limited to, `&str`, `&BStr`, and of course, `&[u8]` itself.

defs.name: into_string
defs.docs:
Converts a `Vec<u8>` into a `String` if and only if this byte string is
 valid UTF-8.

defs.name: into_string_lossy
defs.docs:
Lossily converts a `Vec<u8>` into a `String`. If this byte string
 contains invalid UTF-8, then the invalid bytes are replaced with the
 Unicode replacement codepoint.

defs.name: into_string_unchecked
defs.docs:
Unsafely convert this byte string into a `String`, without checking for
 valid UTF-8.

defs.name: into_os_string
defs.docs: Converts this byte string into an OS string, in place.

defs.name: into_os_string_lossy
defs.docs: Lossily converts this byte string into an OS string, in place.

defs.name: into_path_buf
defs.docs: Converts this byte string into an owned file path, in place.

defs.name: into_path_buf_lossy
defs.docs: Lossily converts this byte string into an owned file path, in place.

defs.name: pop_byte
defs.docs: Removes the last byte from this `Vec<u8>` and returns it.

defs.name: pop_char
defs.docs: Removes the last codepoint from this `Vec<u8>` and returns it.

defs.name: remove_char
defs.docs:
Removes a `char` from this `Vec<u8>` at the given byte position and
 returns it.

defs.name: insert_char
defs.value: fn (&mut self, at: usize, ch: char) -> ()
defs.docs:
Inserts the given codepoint into this `Vec<u8>` at a particular byte
 position.

defs.name: insert_str
defs.value: fn <B> (&mut self, at: usize, bytes: B) -> ()
defs.docs:
Inserts the given byte string into this byte string at a particular
 byte position.

defs.name: replace_range
defs.value: fn <R, B> (&mut self, range: R, replace_with: B) -> ()
defs.docs:
Removes the specified range in this byte string and replaces it with
 the given bytes. The given bytes do not need to have the same length
 as the range provided.

defs.name: drain_bytes
defs.docs:
Creates a draining iterator that removes the specified range in this
 `Vec<u8>` and yields each of the removed bytes.

defs.name: DrainBytes
defs.docs: A draining byte oriented iterator for `Vec<u8>`.

defs.name: FromUtf8Error
defs.docs: An error that may occur when converting a `Vec<u8>` to a `String`.

defs.name: as_bytes
defs.docs:
Return the original bytes as a slice that failed to convert to a
 `String`.

defs.name: into_vec
defs.docs:
Consume this error and return the original byte string that failed to
 convert to a `String`.

defs.name: utf8_error
defs.docs:
Return the underlying UTF-8 error that occurred. This error provides
 information on the nature and location of the invalid UTF-8 detected.

defs.name: io
defs.docs: Utilities for working with I/O using byte strings.

defs.name: BufReadExt
defs.docs:
An extention trait for
 [`std::io::BufRead`](https://doc.rust-lang.org/std/io/trait.BufRead.html)
 which provides convenience APIs for dealing with byte strings.

defs.name: byte_lines
defs.docs:
Returns an iterator over the lines of this reader, where each line
 is represented as a byte string.

defs.name: for_byte_line
defs.docs: Executes the given closure on each line in the underlying reader.

defs.name: for_byte_line_with_terminator
defs.value: fn <F> (mut self, mut for_each_line: F) -> io::Result<()>
defs.docs: Executes the given closure on each line in the underlying reader.

defs.name: ByteLines
defs.docs:
An iterator over lines from an instance of
 [`std::io::BufRead`](https://doc.rust-lang.org/std/io/trait.BufRead.html).

defs.name: Graphemes
defs.docs: An iterator over grapheme clusters in a byte string.

defs.name: as_bytes
defs.docs: View the underlying data as a subslice of the original data.

defs.name: GraphemeIndices
defs.docs:
An iterator over grapheme clusters in a byte string and their byte index
 positions.

defs.name: as_bytes
defs.docs: View the underlying data as a subslice of the original data.

defs.name: Sentences
defs.docs: An iterator over sentences in a byte string.

defs.name: as_bytes
defs.docs: View the underlying data as a subslice of the original data.

defs.name: SentenceIndices
defs.docs: An iterator over sentences in a byte string, along with their byte offsets.

defs.name: as_bytes
defs.docs: View the underlying data as a subslice of the original data.

defs.name: Words
defs.docs: An iterator over words in a byte string.

defs.name: as_bytes
defs.docs: View the underlying data as a subslice of the original data.

defs.name: WordIndices
defs.docs: An iterator over words in a byte string and their byte index positions.

defs.name: as_bytes
defs.docs: View the underlying data as a subslice of the original data.

defs.name: WordsWithBreaks
defs.docs: An iterator over all word breaks in a byte string.

defs.name: as_bytes
defs.docs: View the underlying data as a subslice of the original data.

defs.name: WordsWithBreakIndices
defs.docs:
An iterator over all word breaks in a byte string, along with their byte
 index positions.

defs.name: as_bytes
defs.docs: View the underlying data as a subslice of the original data.

defs.name: Chars
defs.docs: An iterator over Unicode scalar values in a byte string.

defs.name: as_bytes
defs.docs: View the underlying data as a subslice of the original data.

defs.name: CharIndices
defs.docs:
An iterator over Unicode scalar values in a byte string and their
 byte index positions.

defs.name: as_bytes
defs.docs: View the underlying data as a subslice of the original data.

defs.name: Utf8Error
defs.docs: An error that occurs when UTF-8 decoding fails.

defs.name: valid_up_to
defs.docs:
Returns the byte index of the position immediately following the last
 valid UTF-8 byte.

defs.name: error_len
defs.docs:
Returns the total number of invalid UTF-8 bytes immediately following
 the position returned by `valid_up_to`. This value is always at least
 `1`, but can be up to `3` if bytes form a valid prefix of some UTF-8
 encoded codepoint.

defs.name: decode
defs.docs: UTF-8 decode a single Unicode scalar value from the beginning of a slice.

defs.name: decode_last
defs.docs: UTF-8 decode a single Unicode scalar value from the end of a slice.
